Abstract Recent technological advances in optics, computer - aided analysis, and miniaturization have allowed for the development of virtual chromoendoscopy and confo - cal laser endomicroscopy CLE. CLE is based on the use of either a confocal scanning microscope integrated into a conventional flexible endoscope eCLE or endoscope - based CLE or trans - endoscopic probes pCLE or probe - based CLE. Both virtual chromoendoscopic techniques
and CLE have enabled endoscopists to better characterize the gastrointestinal mucosa during endoscopy, and it has sti - mulated significant interest in the application of these techniques in clinical gastroenterology.
This review aims to eva - luate the current data on the technical aspects and the utility of these new technologies in Barrett ’ s esophagus.
Keywords Barrett ’ s esophagus · Virtual chromoendoscopy · Confocal endomicroscopy
